  "prompt": "What are some lesser known facts about PM Narendra Modi?",
  "response": "Here are some lesser-known facts about Prime Minister Narendra Modi:\n\n1. **Early Life and Struggles**: Narendra Modi was born into a modest family in Vadnagar, Gujarat. He helped his father sell tea at the Vadnagar railway station as a child, an experience he often recounts to connect with the common people.\n\n2. **Wandering Monk**: After leaving home at the age of 17, Modi traveled across India for about two years, during which he claims to have lived the life of a wandering monk. This period significantly influenced his spiritual and political outlook.\n\n3. **Connection with RSS**: Modi joined the Rashtriya Swayamsevak Sangh (RSS) at a young age and was deeply involved in its activities. He was a pracharak (full-time worker) for the organization, which played a crucial role in shaping his ideology and political career.\n\n4. **Education and Degrees**: Modi completed his Master's degree in Political Science from Gujarat University. He has also been awarded several honorary doctorates from various universities, both in India and abroad.\n\n5. **Early Political Career**: Before becoming the Chief Minister of Gujarat, Modi held various organizational roles within the BJP. He was instrumental in strengthening the party's presence in Gujarat, which paved the way for his rise to the Chief Minister's position in 2001.\n\n6. **Technological Savvy**: Modi is known for his early adoption of technology in governance. He popularized the use of video conferencing for official meetings even before it became mainstream. He also actively uses social media platforms to engage with citizens, making him one of the most followed world leaders on platforms like Twitter and Instagram.\n\n7. **Environmental Initiatives**: Before becoming the Prime Minister, Modi launched several environmental initiatives in Gujarat, such as the \"Gokul Gram Yojana,\" aimed at preserving indigenous cow breeds. His administration has continued to prioritize environmental conservation, with initiatives like the Swachh Bharat Abhiyan (Clean India Campaign).\n\n8. **International Yoga Day**: Modi proposed the idea of International Yoga Day at the United Nations, which was adopted and is celebrated globally on June 21st each year. This reflects his emphasis on promoting yoga and holistic health.\n\n9. **Author and Columnist**: Modi has authored several books, including \"Jyotipunj,\" a collection of profiles of various RSS workers who inspired him, and \"Exam Warriors,\" a book aimed at helping students manage exam stress.\n\n10. **Philatelic Enthusiast**: Modi has a keen interest in philately (stamp collecting). He has mentioned that collecting stamps helped him learn about different countries and cultures during his childhood.\n\nThese facts provide a glimpse into the varied facets of Narendra Modi's life and career, showcasing his journey from humble beginnings to becoming one of the world's most prominent political figures.",
